100/* The valid defines for all message
101 * types know to SCTP. 0 is reserved
102 */
103#define SCTP_DATA 0x00
104#define SCTP_INITIATION 0x01
105#define SCTP_INITIATION_ACK 0x02
106#define SCTP_SELECTIVE_ACK 0x03
107#define SCTP_HEARTBEAT_REQUEST 0x04
108#define SCTP_HEARTBEAT_ACK 0x05
109#define SCTP_ABORT_ASSOCIATION 0x06
110#define SCTP_SHUTDOWN 0x07
111#define SCTP_SHUTDOWN_ACK 0x08
112#define SCTP_OPERATION_ERR 0x09
113#define SCTP_COOKIE_ECHO 0x0a
114#define SCTP_COOKIE_ACK 0x0b
115#define SCTP_ECN_ECHO 0x0c
116#define SCTP_ECN_CWR 0x0d
117#define SCTP_SHUTDOWN_COMPLETE 0x0e
118#define SCTP_FORWARD_CUM_TSN 0xc0
119#define SCTP_RELIABLE_CNTL 0xc1
120#define SCTP_RELIABLE_CNTL_ACK 0xc2
121
122static const struct tok sctp_chunkid_str[] = {
123 { SCTP_DATA, "DATA" },
124 { SCTP_INITIATION, "INIT" },
125 { SCTP_INITIATION_ACK, "INIT ACK" },
126 { SCTP_SELECTIVE_ACK, "SACK" },
127 { SCTP_HEARTBEAT_REQUEST, "HB REQ" },
128 { SCTP_HEARTBEAT_ACK, "HB ACK" },
129 { SCTP_ABORT_ASSOCIATION, "ABORT" },
130 { SCTP_SHUTDOWN, "SHUTDOWN" },
131 { SCTP_SHUTDOWN_ACK, "SHUTDOWN ACK" },
132 { SCTP_OPERATION_ERR, "OP ERR" },
133 { SCTP_COOKIE_ECHO, "COOKIE ECHO" },
134 { SCTP_COOKIE_ACK, "COOKIE ACK" },
135 { SCTP_ECN_ECHO, "ECN ECHO" },
136 { SCTP_ECN_CWR, "ECN CWR" },
137 { SCTP_SHUTDOWN_COMPLETE, "SHUTDOWN COMPLETE" },
138 { SCTP_FORWARD_CUM_TSN, "FOR CUM TSN" },
139 { SCTP_RELIABLE_CNTL, "REL CTRL" },
140 { SCTP_RELIABLE_CNTL_ACK, "REL CTRL ACK" },
141 { 0, NULL }
142};

144/* Data Chuck Specific Flags */
145#define SCTP_DATA_FRAG_MASK 0x03
146#define SCTP_DATA_MIDDLE_FRAG 0x00
147#define SCTP_DATA_LAST_FRAG 0x01
148#define SCTP_DATA_FIRST_FRAG 0x02
149#define SCTP_DATA_NOT_FRAG 0x03
150#define SCTP_DATA_UNORDERED 0x04
151
152#define SCTP_ADDRMAX 60
153
154#define CHAN_HP 6704
155#define CHAN_MP 6705
156#define CHAN_LP 6706
157
158/* the sctp common header */
159
160struct sctpHeader{
161 uint16_t source;
162 uint16_t destination;
163 uint32_t verificationTag;
164 uint32_t adler32;
165};
166
167/* various descriptor parsers */
168
169struct sctpChunkDesc{
170 uint8_t chunkID;
171 uint8_t chunkFlg;
172 uint16_t chunkLength;
173};
174
175struct sctpParamDesc{
176 uint16_t paramType;
177 uint16_t paramLength;
178};
179
180
181struct sctpRelChunkDesc{
182 struct sctpChunkDesc chk;
183 uint32_t serialNumber;
184};
185
186struct sctpVendorSpecificParam {
187 struct sctpParamDesc p; /* type must be 0xfffe */
188 uint32_t vendorId; /* vendor ID from RFC 1700 */
189 uint16_t vendorSpecificType;
190 uint16_t vendorSpecificLen;
191};
192
193
194/* Structures for the control parts */
195
196
197
198/* Sctp association init request/ack */
199
200/* this is used for init ack, too */
201struct sctpInitiation{
202 uint32_t initTag; /* tag of mine */
203 uint32_t rcvWindowCredit; /* rwnd */
204 uint16_t NumPreopenStreams; /* OS */
205 uint16_t MaxInboundStreams; /* MIS */
206 uint32_t initialTSN;
207 /* optional param's follow in sctpParamDesc form */
208};
209
210struct sctpV4IpAddress{
211 struct sctpParamDesc p; /* type is set to SCTP_IPV4_PARAM_TYPE, len=10 */
212 uint32_t ipAddress;
213};
214
215
216struct sctpV6IpAddress{
217 struct sctpParamDesc p; /* type is set to SCTP_IPV6_PARAM_TYPE, len=22 */
218 uint8_t ipAddress[16];
219};
220
221struct sctpDNSName{
222 struct sctpParamDesc param;
223 uint8_t name[1];
224};
225
226
227struct sctpCookiePreserve{
228 struct sctpParamDesc p; /* type is set to SCTP_COOKIE_PRESERVE, len=8 */
229 uint32_t extraTime;
230};
231
232
233struct sctpTimeStamp{
234 uint32_t ts_sec;
235 uint32_t ts_usec;
236};
237
238/* wire structure of my cookie */
239struct cookieMessage{
240 uint32_t TieTag_curTag; /* copied from assoc if present */
241 uint32_t TieTag_hisTag; /* copied from assoc if present */
242 int32_t cookieLife; /* life I will award this cookie */
243 struct sctpTimeStamp timeEnteringState; /* the time I built cookie */
244 struct sctpInitiation initAckISent; /* the INIT-ACK that I sent to my peer */
245 uint32_t addressWhereISent[4]; /* I make this 4 ints so I get 128bits for future */
246 int32_t addrtype; /* address type */
247 uint16_t locScope; /* V6 local scope flag */
248 uint16_t siteScope; /* V6 site scope flag */
249 /* at the end is tacked on the INIT chunk sent in
250 * its entirety and of course our
251 * signature.
252 */
253};
254
255
256/* this guy is for use when
257 * I have a initiate message gloming the
258 * things together.
259
260 */
261struct sctpUnifiedInit{
262 struct sctpChunkDesc uh;
263 struct sctpInitiation initm;
264};
265
266struct sctpSendableInit{
267 struct sctpHeader mh;
268 struct sctpUnifiedInit msg;
269};
270
271
272/* Selective Acknowledgement
273 * has the following structure with
274 * a optional ammount of trailing int's
275 * on the last part (based on the numberOfDesc
276 * field).
277 */
278
279struct sctpSelectiveAck{
280 uint32_t highestConseqTSN;
281 uint32_t updatedRwnd;
282 uint16_t numberOfdesc;
283 uint16_t numDupTsns;
284};
285
286struct sctpSelectiveFrag{
287 uint16_t fragmentStart;
288 uint16_t fragmentEnd;
289};
290
291
292struct sctpUnifiedSack{
293 struct sctpChunkDesc uh;
294 struct sctpSelectiveAck sack;
295};
296
297/* for both RTT request/response the
298 * following is sent
299 */
300
301struct sctpHBrequest {
302 uint32_t time_value_1;
303 uint32_t time_value_2;
304};
305
306/* here is what I read and respond with to. */
307struct sctpHBunified{
308 struct sctpChunkDesc hdr;
309 struct sctpParamDesc hb;
310};
311
312
313/* here is what I send */
314struct sctpHBsender{
315 struct sctpChunkDesc hdr;
316 struct sctpParamDesc hb;
317 struct sctpHBrequest rtt;
318 int8_t addrFmt[SCTP_ADDRMAX];
319 uint16_t userreq;
320};
321
322
323
324/* for the abort and shutdown ACK
325 * we must carry the init tag in the common header. Just the
326 * common header is all that is needed with a chunk descriptor.
327 */
328struct sctpUnifiedAbort{
329 struct sctpChunkDesc uh;
330};
331
332struct sctpUnifiedAbortLight{
333 struct sctpHeader mh;
334 struct sctpChunkDesc uh;
335};
336
337struct sctpUnifiedAbortHeavy{
338 struct sctpHeader mh;
339 struct sctpChunkDesc uh;
340 uint16_t causeCode;
341 uint16_t causeLen;
342};
343
344/* For the graceful shutdown we must carry
345 * the tag (in common header) and the highest consequitive acking value
346 */
347struct sctpShutdown {
348 uint32_t TSN_Seen;
349};
350
351struct sctpUnifiedShutdown{
352 struct sctpChunkDesc uh;
353 struct sctpShutdown shut;
354};
355
356/* in the unified message we add the trailing
357 * stream id since it is the only message
358 * that is defined as a operation error.
359 */
360struct sctpOpErrorCause{
361 uint16_t cause;
362 uint16_t causeLen;
363};
364
365struct sctpUnifiedOpError{
366 struct sctpChunkDesc uh;
367 struct sctpOpErrorCause c;
368};
369
370struct sctpUnifiedStreamError{
371 struct sctpHeader mh;
372 struct sctpChunkDesc uh;
373 struct sctpOpErrorCause c;
374 uint16_t strmNum;
375 uint16_t reserved;
376};
377
378struct staleCookieMsg{
379 struct sctpHeader mh;
380 struct sctpChunkDesc uh;
381 struct sctpOpErrorCause c;
382 uint32_t moretime;
383};
384
385/* the following is used in all sends
386 * where nothing is needed except the
387 * chunk/type i.e. shutdownAck Abort */
388
389struct sctpUnifiedSingleMsg{
390 struct sctpHeader mh;
391 struct sctpChunkDesc uh;
392};
393
394struct sctpDataPart{
395 uint32_t TSN;
396 uint16_t streamId;
397 uint16_t sequence;
398 uint32_t payloadtype;
399};
400
401struct sctpUnifiedDatagram{
402 struct sctpChunkDesc uh;
403 struct sctpDataPart dp;
404};
405
406struct sctpECN_echo{
407 struct sctpChunkDesc uh;
408 uint32_t Lowest_TSN;
409};
410
411
412struct sctpCWR{
413 struct sctpChunkDesc uh;
414 uint32_t TSN_reduced_at;
415};

486static inline int isForCES_port(u_short Port)
487{
488 if (Port == CHAN_HP)
489 return 1;
490 if (Port == CHAN_MP)
491 return 1;
492 if (Port == CHAN_LP)
493 return 1;
494
495 return 0;
496}
497
498void sctp_print(netdissect_options *ndo,
499 const u_char *bp, /* beginning of sctp packet */
500 const u_char *bp2, /* beginning of enclosing */
501 u_int sctpPacketLength) /* ip packet */
502{
503 u_int sctpPacketLengthRemaining;
504 const struct sctpHeader *sctpPktHdr;
505 const struct ip *ip;
506 const struct ip6_hdr *ip6;
507 u_short sourcePort, destPort;
508 int chunkCount;
509 const struct sctpChunkDesc *chunkDescPtr;
510 const char *sep;
511 int isforces = 0;
512
513 if (sctpPacketLength < sizeof(struct sctpHeader))
514 {
515 ND_PRINT((ndo, "truncated-sctp - %ld bytes missing!",
516 (long)(sizeof(struct sctpHeader) - sctpPacketLength)));
517 return;
518 }
519 sctpPktHdr = (const struct sctpHeader*) bp;
520 ND_TCHECK(*sctpPktHdr);
521 sctpPacketLengthRemaining = sctpPacketLength;
522
523 sourcePort = EXTRACT_16BITS(&sctpPktHdr->source);
524 destPort = EXTRACT_16BITS(&sctpPktHdr->destination);
525
526 ip = (const struct ip *)bp2;
527 if (IP_V(ip) == 6)
528 ip6 = (const struct ip6_hdr *)bp2;
529 else
530 ip6 = NULL;
531
532 if (ip6) {
533 ND_PRINT((ndo, "%s.%d > %s.%d: sctp",
534 ip6addr_string(ndo, &ip6->ip6_src),
535 sourcePort,
536 ip6addr_string(ndo, &ip6->ip6_dst),
537 destPort));
538 } else
539 {
540 ND_PRINT((ndo, "%s.%d > %s.%d: sctp",
541 ipaddr_string(ndo, &ip->ip_src),
542 sourcePort,
543 ipaddr_string(ndo, &ip->ip_dst),
544 destPort));
545 }
546
547 if (isForCES_port(sourcePort)) {
548 ND_PRINT((ndo, "[%s]", tok2str(ForCES_channels, NULL, sourcePort)));
549 isforces = 1;
550 }
551 if (isForCES_port(destPort)) {
552 ND_PRINT((ndo, "[%s]", tok2str(ForCES_channels, NULL, destPort)));
553 isforces = 1;
554 }
555
556 bp += sizeof(struct sctpHeader);
557 sctpPacketLengthRemaining -= sizeof(struct sctpHeader);
558
559 if (ndo->ndo_vflag >= 2)
560 sep = "\n\t";
561 else
562 sep = " (";
563 /* cycle through all chunks, printing information on each one */
564 for (chunkCount = 0, chunkDescPtr = (const struct sctpChunkDesc *)bp;
565 sctpPacketLengthRemaining != 0;
566 chunkCount++)
567 {
568 uint16_t chunkLength, chunkLengthRemaining;
569 uint16_t align;
570
571 chunkDescPtr = (const struct sctpChunkDesc *)bp;
572 if (sctpPacketLengthRemaining < sizeof(*chunkDescPtr)) {
573 ND_PRINT((ndo, "%s%d) [chunk descriptor cut off at end of packet]", sep, chunkCount+1));
574 break;
575 }
576 ND_TCHECK(*chunkDescPtr);
577 chunkLength = EXTRACT_16BITS(&chunkDescPtr->chunkLength);
578 if (chunkLength < sizeof(*chunkDescPtr)) {
579 ND_PRINT((ndo, "%s%d) [Bad chunk length %u, < size of chunk descriptor]", sep, chunkCount+1, chunkLength));
580 break;
581 }
582 chunkLengthRemaining = chunkLength;
583
584 align = chunkLength % 4;
585 if (align != 0)
586 align = 4 - align;
587
588 if (sctpPacketLengthRemaining < align) {
589 ND_PRINT((ndo, "%s%d) [Bad chunk length %u, > remaining data in packet]", sep, chunkCount+1, chunkLength));
590 break;
591 }
592
593 ND_TCHECK2(*bp, chunkLength);
594
595 bp += sizeof(*chunkDescPtr);
596 sctpPacketLengthRemaining -= sizeof(*chunkDescPtr);
597 chunkLengthRemaining -= sizeof(*chunkDescPtr);
598
599 ND_PRINT((ndo, "%s%d) ", sep, chunkCount+1));
600 ND_PRINT((ndo, "[%s] ", tok2str(sctp_chunkid_str, "Unknown chunk type: 0x%x",
601 chunkDescPtr->chunkID)));
602 switch (chunkDescPtr->chunkID)
603 {
604 case SCTP_DATA :
605 {
606 const struct sctpDataPart *dataHdrPtr;
607 uint32_t ppid;
608 u_int payload_size;
609
610 if ((chunkDescPtr->chunkFlg & SCTP_DATA_UNORDERED)
611 == SCTP_DATA_UNORDERED)
612 ND_PRINT((ndo, "(U)"));
613
614 if ((chunkDescPtr->chunkFlg & SCTP_DATA_FIRST_FRAG)
615 == SCTP_DATA_FIRST_FRAG)
616 ND_PRINT((ndo, "(B)"));
617
618 if ((chunkDescPtr->chunkFlg & SCTP_DATA_LAST_FRAG)
619 == SCTP_DATA_LAST_FRAG)
620 ND_PRINT((ndo, "(E)"));
621
622 if( ((chunkDescPtr->chunkFlg & SCTP_DATA_UNORDERED)
623 == SCTP_DATA_UNORDERED)
624 ||
625 ((chunkDescPtr->chunkFlg & SCTP_DATA_FIRST_FRAG)
626 == SCTP_DATA_FIRST_FRAG)
627 ||
628 ((chunkDescPtr->chunkFlg & SCTP_DATA_LAST_FRAG)
629 == SCTP_DATA_LAST_FRAG) )
630 ND_PRINT((ndo, " "));
631
632 if (chunkLengthRemaining < sizeof(*dataHdrPtr)) {
633 ND_PRINT((ndo, "bogus chunk length %u]", chunkLength));
634 return;
635 }
636 dataHdrPtr=(const struct sctpDataPart*)bp;
637
638 ppid = EXTRACT_32BITS(&dataHdrPtr->payloadtype);
639 ND_PRINT((ndo, "[TSN: %u] ", EXTRACT_32BITS(&dataHdrPtr->TSN)));
640 ND_PRINT((ndo, "[SID: %u] ", EXTRACT_16BITS(&dataHdrPtr->streamId)));
641 ND_PRINT((ndo, "[SSEQ %u] ", EXTRACT_16BITS(&dataHdrPtr->sequence)));
642 ND_PRINT((ndo, "[PPID %s] ",
643 tok2str(PayloadProto_idents, "0x%x", ppid)));
644
645 if (!isforces) {
646 isforces = (ppid == SCTP_PPID_FORCES_HP) ||
647 (ppid == SCTP_PPID_FORCES_MP) ||
648 (ppid == SCTP_PPID_FORCES_LP);
649 }
650
651 bp += sizeof(*dataHdrPtr);
652 sctpPacketLengthRemaining -= sizeof(*dataHdrPtr);
653 chunkLengthRemaining -= sizeof(*dataHdrPtr);
654 payload_size = chunkLengthRemaining;
655 if (payload_size == 0) {
656 ND_PRINT((ndo, "bogus chunk length %u]", chunkLength));
657 return;
658 }
659
660 if (isforces) {
661 forces_print(ndo, bp, payload_size);
662 } else if (ndo->ndo_vflag >= 2) { /* if verbose output is specified */
663 /* at the command line */
664 switch (ppid) {
665 case SCTP_PPID_M3UA :
666 m3ua_print(ndo, bp, payload_size);
667 break;
668 default:
669 ND_PRINT((ndo, "[Payload"));
670 if (!ndo->ndo_suppress_default_print) {
671 ND_PRINT((ndo, ":"));
672 ND_DEFAULTPRINT(bp, payload_size);
673 }
674 ND_PRINT((ndo, "]"));
675 break;
676 }
677 }
678 bp += payload_size;
679 sctpPacketLengthRemaining -= payload_size;
680 chunkLengthRemaining -= payload_size;
681 break;
682 }
683 case SCTP_INITIATION :
684 {
685 const struct sctpInitiation *init;
686
687 if (chunkLengthRemaining < sizeof(*init)) {
688 ND_PRINT((ndo, "bogus chunk length %u]", chunkLength));
689 return;
690 }
691 init=(const struct sctpInitiation*)bp;
692 ND_PRINT((ndo, "[init tag: %u] ", EXTRACT_32BITS(&init->initTag)));
693 ND_PRINT((ndo, "[rwnd: %u] ", EXTRACT_32BITS(&init->rcvWindowCredit)));
694 ND_PRINT((ndo, "[OS: %u] ", EXTRACT_16BITS(&init->NumPreopenStreams)));
695 ND_PRINT((ndo, "[MIS: %u] ", EXTRACT_16BITS(&init->MaxInboundStreams)));
696 ND_PRINT((ndo, "[init TSN: %u] ", EXTRACT_32BITS(&init->initialTSN)));
697 bp += sizeof(*init);
698 sctpPacketLengthRemaining -= sizeof(*init);
699 chunkLengthRemaining -= sizeof(*init);
700
701#if 0 /* ALC you can add code for optional params here */
702 if( chunkLengthRemaining != 0 )
703 ND_PRINT((ndo, " @@@@@ UNFINISHED @@@@@@%s\n",
704 "Optional params present, but not printed."));
705#endif
706 bp += chunkLengthRemaining;
707 sctpPacketLengthRemaining -= chunkLengthRemaining;
708 chunkLengthRemaining = 0;
709 break;
710 }
711 case SCTP_INITIATION_ACK :
712 {
713 const struct sctpInitiation *init;
714
715 if (chunkLengthRemaining < sizeof(*init)) {
716 ND_PRINT((ndo, "bogus chunk length %u]", chunkLength));
717 return;
718 }
719 init=(const struct sctpInitiation*)bp;
720 ND_PRINT((ndo, "[init tag: %u] ", EXTRACT_32BITS(&init->initTag)));
721 ND_PRINT((ndo, "[rwnd: %u] ", EXTRACT_32BITS(&init->rcvWindowCredit)));
722 ND_PRINT((ndo, "[OS: %u] ", EXTRACT_16BITS(&init->NumPreopenStreams)));
723 ND_PRINT((ndo, "[MIS: %u] ", EXTRACT_16BITS(&init->MaxInboundStreams)));
724 ND_PRINT((ndo, "[init TSN: %u] ", EXTRACT_32BITS(&init->initialTSN)));
725 bp += sizeof(*init);
726 sctpPacketLengthRemaining -= sizeof(*init);
727 chunkLengthRemaining -= sizeof(*init);
728
729#if 0 /* ALC you can add code for optional params here */
730 if( chunkLengthRemaining != 0 )
731 ND_PRINT((ndo, " @@@@@ UNFINISHED @@@@@@%s\n",
732 "Optional params present, but not printed."));
733#endif
734 bp += chunkLengthRemaining;
735 sctpPacketLengthRemaining -= chunkLengthRemaining;
736 chunkLengthRemaining = 0;
737 break;
738 }
739 case SCTP_SELECTIVE_ACK:
740 {
741 const struct sctpSelectiveAck *sack;
742 const struct sctpSelectiveFrag *frag;
743 int fragNo, tsnNo;
744 const u_char *dupTSN;
745
746 if (chunkLengthRemaining < sizeof(*sack)) {
747 ND_PRINT((ndo, "bogus chunk length %u]", chunkLength));
748 return;
749 }
750 sack=(const struct sctpSelectiveAck*)bp;
751 ND_PRINT((ndo, "[cum ack %u] ", EXTRACT_32BITS(&sack->highestConseqTSN)));
752 ND_PRINT((ndo, "[a_rwnd %u] ", EXTRACT_32BITS(&sack->updatedRwnd)));
753 ND_PRINT((ndo, "[#gap acks %u] ", EXTRACT_16BITS(&sack->numberOfdesc)));
754 ND_PRINT((ndo, "[#dup tsns %u] ", EXTRACT_16BITS(&sack->numDupTsns)));
755 bp += sizeof(*sack);
756 sctpPacketLengthRemaining -= sizeof(*sack);
757 chunkLengthRemaining -= sizeof(*sack);
758
759
760 /* print gaps */
761 for (fragNo=0;
762 chunkLengthRemaining != 0 && fragNo < EXTRACT_16BITS(&sack->numberOfdesc);
763 bp += sizeof(*frag), sctpPacketLengthRemaining -= sizeof(*frag), chunkLengthRemaining -= sizeof(*frag), fragNo++) {
764 if (chunkLengthRemaining < sizeof(*frag)) {
765 ND_PRINT((ndo, "bogus chunk length %u]", chunkLength));
766 return;
767 }
768 frag = (const struct sctpSelectiveFrag *)bp;
769 ND_PRINT((ndo, "\n\t\t[gap ack block #%d: start = %u, end = %u] ",
770 fragNo+1,
771 EXTRACT_32BITS(&sack->highestConseqTSN) + EXTRACT_16BITS(&frag->fragmentStart),
772 EXTRACT_32BITS(&sack->highestConseqTSN) + EXTRACT_16BITS(&frag->fragmentEnd)));
773 }
774
775 /* print duplicate TSNs */
776 for (tsnNo=0;
777 chunkLengthRemaining != 0 && tsnNo<EXTRACT_16BITS(&sack->numDupTsns);
778 bp += 4, sctpPacketLengthRemaining -= 4, chunkLengthRemaining -= 4, tsnNo++) {
779 if (chunkLengthRemaining < 4) {
780 ND_PRINT((ndo, "bogus chunk length %u]", chunkLength));
781 return;
782 }
783 dupTSN = (const u_char *)bp;
784 ND_PRINT((ndo, "\n\t\t[dup TSN #%u: %u] ", tsnNo+1,
785 EXTRACT_32BITS(dupTSN)));
786 }
787 break;
788 }
789 default :
790 {
791 bp += chunkLengthRemaining;
792 sctpPacketLengthRemaining -= chunkLengthRemaining;
793 chunkLengthRemaining = 0;
794 break;
795 }
796 }
797
798 /*
799 * Any extra stuff at the end of the chunk?
800 * XXX - report this?
801 */
802 bp += chunkLengthRemaining;
803 sctpPacketLengthRemaining -= chunkLengthRemaining;
804
805 if (ndo->ndo_vflag < 2)
806 sep = ", (";
807
808 if (align != 0) {
809 /*
810 * Fail if the alignment padding isn't in the captured data.
811 * Otherwise, skip it.
812 */
813 ND_TCHECK2(*bp, align);
814 bp += align;
815 sctpPacketLengthRemaining -= align;
816 }
817 }
818 return;
819
820trunc:
821 ND_PRINT((ndo, "[|sctp]"));
822}
